During 1992-4, I commuted between Berkeley and Lodi CA, and on Sundays, I stopped at Grizzly Island and birded.  I crawled under the gate by the port a potties, birded the little pond, then crossed the single lane bridge and went to the Rush Ranch Visitor Center, and hiked through the trees, to the top of the hill.  Then I drove the long and windy road past the tule elk, to parallel the windy slough.  Often, I'd stop at the BBQ place, get ribs, and bring them to the Rush Ranch picnic tables and eat.  Then, I'd be on my way back to Lodi.  Because I was new to birding and to this area, the birds I did see and looked up in the field guides, made a big impression on me, and many of the scenes, I still remember vividly.
